Sentencas: Conductive La0.8Sr0.2MnO3 (LSM) and La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3 (LSCF) layers with a thickness of similar to 10 mu m were deposited on ferritic stainless steel (SS) by the aerosol deposition method, for use as an oxidation resistance-coating layer in the metallic interconnector of a solid oxide fuel cell.
Titulo: Oxidation resistance coating of LSM and LSCF on SOFC metallic interconnects by the aerosol deposition process

Sentencas: The coated layers were fairly dense without pores or cracks, and maintained good adhesion even after oxidation at 800 degrees C for 100 h. The surface of the bare SS after annealing at 800 degrees C for 100 h was covered with Cr2O3 and Fe3O4 oxide scales, and the electrical conductivity was sharply decreased.
Titulo: Oxidation resistance coating of LSM and LSCF on SOFC metallic interconnects by the aerosol deposition process

Sentencas: However, the LSM- and LSCF-coated SSs showed a surface microstructure with almost no oxidation and maintained good electrical conductivity after annealing at 800 degrees C for 100 h. The area-specific resistance (ASR) of LSM- and LSCF-coated alloys after 100 h of oxidation at 800 degrees C was 20.6 and 11.7 m Omega.cm(2), respectively.
Titulo: Oxidation resistance coating of LSM and LSCF on SOFC metallic interconnects by the aerosol deposition process
